data.title: Changed GUI text to better match action
data.body:
Seems how you are creating a node not opening one it would make more sense to have the GUI say create rather than open.

I have built and tested this change and it works ;)

data.title: Exported apk from linux crashes
data.body:
There seems to be a regression (at least in my case) of the export to android functionality, the machine that i'm currently using runs Arch Linux x86_64.
Unfortunately i wasn't able to track the exact commit that introduced the regression and if i check the output of Godot while it is exporting there are no errors, the only thing that i know for sure is that it was introduced some commit after this [one](https://github.com/okamstudio/godot/commit/642c63319eb7471c9accc0c50dfffef5d72c0078).
Has someone else experienced this problem?

data.title: 2D pathfinding bugous
data.body:
As it is stated in http://devmaster.net/devdb/engines/godot godot engine supports 2D pathfinding and I think if devs read that, at some extent they count on it.

When you put hands on it, you see a different picture:

1) It no where documented have to use it. 
2) The only info that I could find is in this forum thread http://www.godotengine.org/forum/viewtopic.php?f=11&t=625&start=10 where the conclusion is that it doesn't work at all (THATS THE ISSUE).
3) Anyway the concept with pathway alpha maps seems wrong. Every time I put some static object (for ex. a house) on my map, I have to redraw the alpha some-have, and it's not dynamic at all (for ex. if the house moves at run-time). 

So are there any plans to implement a collider based Pathfinding. One that takes in account collisions and tries to get around them? Or a plan to fix this with alfa maps?

data.title: [FIX] "File->Save As" in Script panel
data.body:
I have fixed "File->Save As.." in Script panel. I've just put working code from dock 'save as' out to function which is used by editor, and made dock use it when 'saving as'.

Tested on Archlinux and OS X.

data.title: Fix http response and user directory
data.body:
Fix http read response body size mismatch
Fix user directory does not correct created under windows platform.

HTTPClient::read_response_body_chunk -> set result size to received size
DirAccess::make_dir_recursive -> ignore E_CANT_CREATE error

data.title: enable keypad navigation in text editor
data.body: With NumLock disabled, the keypad should allow the secondary functions in the text editor. For some laptops, this is the only way to use functions such as Home/End/PgUp/PgDn, for example.

data.body:
At the following URL, https://github.com/okamstudio/godot/wiki/tutorial_scene, there is a grammatical error in a list under the 'Nodes' section, fifth item down: 

Can be added other nodes as children.
should be
Can be added to other nodes as children.

data.title: Visual graph editor is not enabled.
KinematicBody strange issue
data.body:
Curious thing, when I was positioned the KinematicBody in arbitrary coordinates using GridMap with collisions all work fine.
But using a large plane or a grid for collision only on a mesh terrain and place KinematicBody on arbitrary coordinates in little times the system is overloaded and a terrible lag begins!
But if I start KinematicBody from corrdinates 0,0,0  the issue don't appears!
I'll still do more testing to confirm it in more cases.
